<title>USA: Lillian Vernon takes steps for UPS strike.</title>
<headline>Lillian Vernon takes steps for UPS strike.</headline>
<dateline>NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. 1997-08-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lillian Vernon Corp said on Monday it had made arrangements with other shippers in order to minimize the impact of a strike by United Parcel Service of America Inc on its customers.</p>
<p>The specialty catalog company said it had been in touch with the Office of the Postmaster General of the U.S. Postal Service and other delivery vendors, who assured Lillian Vernon they would try to accommodate its mail and package shipments.</p>
<p>Lillian Vernon said it was also keeping customers informed of potential delays in orders caused by the strike.</p>
<p>The walkout by union drivers, loaders and package sorters working for UPS began at 1201 EDT/0401 GMT Monday, after a efforts to set a new five-year contract in Washington collapsed over differences on pay, benefits and job security.</p>
<p>((New York newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
